  "programNotes": "<ul> <li>Completion of a field school as an EOS elective is recommended. EOS <a href=\"#/courses/Sy8n7_a74\">300</a> requires that EOS <a href=\"#/courses/H1V3XuTX4\">202</a> be taken as an elective. EOS <a href=\"#/courses/S1oIB9G_N\">401</a> requires two of <a href=\"#/courses/Syuhm_TmE\">312</a>, <a href=\"#/courses/B1dh7_T7V\">313</a> or (<a href=\"#/courses/S1tn7d6QE\">314</a> or <a href=\"#/courses/ryWamu67N\">431</a>) be taken as electives.</li> <li>Most 400-level EOS classes are offered in alternate years. A schedule of when each class is offered is available on the <a href=\"https://www.uvic.ca/science/seos/index.php\">School of Earth and Ocean Sciences website</a>.</li> </ul>",
